                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Greetings all,
<br />

<br />
      I am currently the guild leader of a very small family guild on Tunare server. We will never be true raiders, but to provide some type of goal for our guild, we've recently adopted Seru progression as our guild project. It will be many moons before we are able to take him down, but looking ahead, I see the need to establish raid loot rules.
<br />

<br />
    First, in order to work up to Seru, as many of you know, there is quite a bit of work (and yes I know he can be done without bane weapons etc, but we will be working on as many bane weapons as we can, for our melees). After all this work, I'd hate for someone who opted out of the farming for all the component stuff to win something over a member who worked long and hard helping every chance they got. And we never force anyone in our guild to do anything they don't want to.
<br />

<br />
     I don't want complicated point systems, or anything too extravagant, btu basically I'd like to know how many raid loot systems work. Like DKP or others. And what have been some effective systems for smaller guilds/progression? Could some of you elaborate on this? Like for DKP, is the amount of points for a kill decided by the raid leader? Guild leader? And how are points awarded? This is all new to me, so i am a bit confuzzled.
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance!
<br />

<br />
Fading Illusion
<br />
Guild Leader</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
