                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><a href="http://www.eqdkp.com" target="_blank">www.eqdkp.com</a> is a nice out of the box DKP point system.
<br />

<br />
The basic rundow of any dkp system is you get a points per mob you kill.  Some guilds have rule variations like double points for a guild first, no points for a loss etc.  Each item is assed a point value, the best item your guild is capable of is the highest and it scales down from there.
<br />

<br />
I will use my guild as a example, our best item for any slot is 1500dkp points.  Any one groupable item is 150 points, augments are 250 points. 
<br />
Any class specific item is limited to 1k points and any offhand only weapon is limited to 1200 points.  1 loot per day.
<br />
As far as kills most targets range from 30-60 points per kill.   Any where you can have a intermedite marker, like for example rallos zek, you divide the total points so say the whole enounter was 90 points you would get 30 for the clearing/the triggers, 30 for the brothers and 30 for the kill itself.
<br />
Prices are set, other guilds may use a bidding system but I find it unfair.
<br />
An officer calls out loot and the point value and the person with the most total points wins the item.  If their points are within 100 they random to see who wins.  If no mains wants it then goes into rot status where people can bid for alts or they can bid if they already won a loot or apps can bid on it.  If still no one wants a officer loots and it is destroyed.
<br />
Some guilds put unfair point values on certin weapons they deem better for certin classes (daggers and bows and certin agro weapons most notably)  this is another unfair system as well.  Favortism is avoided if you have a set price and if your class can equip you can bid.  Period.
<br />

<br />
It takes a lot of tweaking to make it work for you.  Each guild is different and you don't want to have to raid 4 months for one item.  Generally speaking it takes us 2 weeks of raiding to aquire 1500 points.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Llan2193 on Mon Apr 04, 2005 7:57 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
