                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The basics are covered here.  My only word of advice is, do not default anything.  It's okay to set up raids for specific people's epics, that is a little different.   Just don't default rare or good drops to anyone.
<br />

<br />
Sleeper's Tomb keys are a good example.  I have been in a couple of small guilds where defaults were set up for Sleeper's Tomb keys.
<br />

<br />
The people who raided the most, generally got the defaults.  Nothing wrong with that on the face of it.  In theory it would mean that the drops would be on people who were generally at raids.  However, the people who raided the most were also the first to get tired of the small guild and move on to a raiding guild.  Everyone who got a Sleeper's Tomb key was gone within two months.  This also happened with the aggro hammer off Xanamech (when that was a big thing).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
