                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It doesn't have to be very complicated.
<br />

<br />
The guild i am in uses a DKP system where you can bid as many points as you have on an item. there is a minimum bid price (in our case, 20 for stuff we normally raid). The advantage to using a system that has this idea at the foundation is that it rewards the frequent raider while at the same time enabling the more casual raider to get loot by saving thier DKP>
<br />

<br />
We have bids going to two people on the DKP councik to ensure accuracy. We use an hourly bonus for long events, we have a first kill bonus of 1.5 times the mobs value, etc.
<br />

<br />
The important thing IMO is that everyone gets a fiar chance. I've seen other systems where there were set prices for items, and the person with the most DKP got the item. Needless to say, this variation makes it very hard to get loot if you aren't in the upper part of the guilds DKP syandings.
<br />

<br />
GL and feel free to ask more questions if you need to</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Starmist
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=520295" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">magelo profile</span></a>
<br />
Alliance of Hope
<br />
Zebuxorak</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
