                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Llan2193 wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Personally I think bidding systems are unfair.
<br />

<br />
Example:  
<br />
First raid of time, Etheral Silk Leggs drop at the time there are only 10 casters in guild
<br />

<br />
Two months later same item drops, but inbetween this time the guild increased its count t 15, same item, now the 2nd person has to pay more simply because the guild recruited more of said class type that did nothing but pad the auction.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The demand for the silk legs went up.  It is now more relatively rare, and apparently more in demand.
<br />

<br />
Why shouldn't the price go up?
<br />

<br />
Those extra people obviously did more than just pad the auction.  They contributed to guild success, for which they earned DKP, and for which they are willing to sacrafice to buy those legs.
<br />

<br />
Bid what you want to pay for an item.  If it is too low, you are happy, because somebody else offered more "DKP effort units" than you are willing to pay.  If you win, you are happy, because that is what you are willing to pay.
<br />

<br />
The problem with bid systems is
<br />
A&gt; Jealosy.
<br />
B&gt; People are rewarded for being better at bidding.
<br />

<br />
More wonkey options:
<br />

<br />
When an item is looted, 25% of the DKP spent is shared amoung all those who could equip the item, and 25% of the DKP spent is allocated amount everyone at the raid.
<br />

<br />
In addition, you get paid (0.5 to 2.0 DKP)/hour of raid attendance.  (2.0 for progression down to 0.5 for minor)
<br />

<br />
So if silk legs drop, the silk classes compete for who gets it.  1/4 of the DKP spent is split amoung all of the silk classes present.
<br />

<br />
This means if you are 'screwed' because someone bids up your silk armor constantly, you can use that screwage to buy other items.  =)</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
