                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My old guild on Luclin used the Loot Council system.  About the time I retired, we were ready to break into Elemental or attempt Emp Ssra.  With the OoW focus scaling, Emp / VT never happened.  Anyhow - we raided quite frequently (about half the guild and most melee were keyed for ST and got a primal weapon), as many as 3-4 times per week.
<br />

<br />
For me, I had some initial suspicions about the system.  Some individual decisions were not unanimous, and certainly questionable.  If you try it for 3-4 months though, I guarantee you will never consider a DKP system.  It works out in the end to be fair for all.  Biggest decision influencer for us was always when someone last received loot.  Knowing this, most people didn't send tells for minor upgrades.  Tradeable gear (like BoCs) was always considered guild property and expected to be returned upon de-guilding/retirement.
<br />

<br />
Anyhow, here's the scoop on it from our website:
<br />

<br />
House of Aegis uses a Loot Council (LC). Loot Council is just as the name denotes. A council in which loot is discussed and distributed by a pre-determined fashion. However, LC has the added advantage of the flexibility that comes with the human element. In a points system, actions of merit, extra work, and other things are not noted. It is run almost solely off raid attendance.
<br />

<br />
The LC method of loot distribution works for the overall growth of the guild. Instead of having a half dozen people have the absolute best gear the guild gets, the entire guild will benefit from drops, bringing the guild players' equipment level with each other. This also allows users of an LC to put equipment where it is needed most, and can benefit the guild the most. There will of course be players who are better equipped, but for the most part, the disparity between equipment levels should not be glaring.
<br />

<br />
Decisions on loot are made based on a number of factors including but not limited to: how much it will improve the player, class, level, raid attendance, and certain non-tangible things. By non-tangible we mean passing on items they need, so others can have... organizing raids... playing multiple characters, or other peoples' when the guild needs...keeping the guild in a positive attitude... organizing fun things to do... scouting mobs... doing faction work with other people... any work done for the guild beyond normal raiding/grouping... researching mobs/strats... doing ports... going to other zones to rez guildies... going out of your way to help someone... donation of items to guild for distribution etc etc, you get the idea.
<br />

<br />
The easiest way for a member to improve his chance on an item is to attend raids (obviously you can't get an item if you're not there!), or doing one of the many, many things that make a guild click and whirr. If you think you are not being noticed, or overlooked, for goodness sakes let us know! Also, if you see someone going above and beyond, let us know about them, we can't see everything! (contrary to popular belief).
<br />

<br />
The final thing about Loot Council is this: It is not perfect. Let me make that clear...
<br />

<br />
Loot Council is run by human beings, so it is not perfect. We will make mistakes.
<br />

<br />
Everyone must have faith that the LC has the interests of the ENTIRE guild on their mind. Distributing loot can be very very difficult. Please remember that we are all friends, and that we are all working towards the same thing.
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
PROCEDURE FOR WHEN LOOT DROPS 
<br />
When an item drops, LC will announce it and ask for tells of those who are interested. Only bid on an item if you really want it, because one of the factors for awarding loot may be "when was the last time member_XX got loot?". That said, if you request the item, you must tell the LC what the item will replace. This is yet another criterion used for loot distribution (how much the item will improve the member).
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
TRICKLE DOWN SYSTEM 
<br />
LC almost always works in conjunction with a Trickle Down System (TDS). What that means is say... Warrior_1 is our #1 warrior and has a Cobalt BP. Warrior_2 is our #2 warrior and has a Tree Weave. One day we drop the statue, and a BP of Eradication drops. Then we award the bp to the #1 warrior (parameters allowing, of course) and warrior #1 gives his cobalt bp to warrior #2. This is mandatory. The only exception is if the item is self-bought. IE, warrior #1 bought the cobalt bp himself. In that case he/she can do what they want with it, sell it... give it to someone, destroy it, keep it etc.
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
JOINT RAIDS AND APPLICANTS 
<br />
For Joint Raids: All participants will be treated as guild members. I.e. If we are doing a joint raid with Leaders of the New School then they have every right to the loot as we do. All factors used to distribute loot will be employed.
<br />

<br />
Applicants: Applicants will be also be treated as guild members, but they will be at a disadvantage, being they are not in guild, and a lot of the factors used to distribute loot will be impossible to track. That said, any applicant can shine and go above and beyond the call of duty, so much so that they can be awarded loot over a normal guild member.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nokei Orhaste &lt;Retired&gt; E66.191/L h++ 2.8khp 4.6km ft12 BK10</a></span>
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?24364" target="_blank" class="postlink">Mirabelle - Foresaken Rogue - Mal`Ganis</a>
<br />
<a href="http://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?33981" target="_blank" class="postlink">Lucies - Priest alt</a>
