                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Like I said, I personal do not think bidding is a fair system.  Yes each person can bid what they want, but I'd rather go off a set point guide.
<br />
I think it favors new memebers more than old, esp if they join when a guild is breaking into new content.
<br />
But I'm not going to debate it, it is nothing more than preference.
<br />

<br />
I like DKP set points because I knew I was getting SoV when it dropped, I knew I was getting a robe of destruction when it dropped, I was at more raids, had more points.  I didnt have to worry about spending all my DKP for one rare item.
<br />

<br />
As far as loot council, having people make decisions on who gets what is bound to have problems.  Also when you start getting 40+ drops a night it makes it very difficult to decide who gets what.
