                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thank you all for all the wonderful replies and lay-outs of different DKP systems. Many of the DKP systems are just way too complicated to be useful by our very small guild, but I applaud guilds and raid leaders who have to sort all that out. Wow.
<br />

<br />
I believe the Loot Council would suit our purposes just fine (yeah, i know that it can have its problems too). We do not raid often at all (one raid every week to 2 weeks), and it seems to be the most laid back, similar to our guild playstyle.
<br />

<br />
For Loot Councils, how many were on the council. How did you vote?
<br />

<br />
As I can see it, here is how I would set it up...a Loot Council, made up of 2-6 people, who are all in a LC channel. For drops, if a person wants that drop, they send a tell to a specific Loot Concilperson along with the item they are upgrading. Those items are listed in the LC channel along with teh person for ho it would be an upgrade. I would follow similar decision making procedures (using attendance, upgradability and recently obtained loot) as Nokei laid out (that system seems most appealing). As for actually deciding who gets what. Not sure if we shoudl vote, or should their be a majority, should there be veto power by RL etc. Any ideas?
<br />

<br />
Some additional background info : We raid once every week to two weeks, and are working on Seru progression (which will take time for us, farming bane and building up more members) with some small mini raids in between (things like Overlord Ngrub in Torg mines,  Nadox Innoruuk, THO (later) and Burrower Beast (later as well)).
<br />

<br />
Fading</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
