                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">PoP flag mobs all dropped upgrades so it never really came up.  We never had the numbers to flag past MM and RD into Sol Ro.  Our largest raids were 24 players.
<br />

<br />
I was looking into this issue before we lost too many members to continue and probably would have assigned a specific value to the flag itself.  Those gaining it would have had to pay that value as if it was loot they won.  Items like the Seru BP ended up going for 1000 to 2000 points.  Most upgrades were in the 200 to 500 range.  Specrals dropped from 400 to about 20 over time which meant new members got their spells fast if we were raiding in PoP.  I'm guessing a flag would have probably been worth about 500 points although some flags are tougher then others.  RD and MM for instance are much harder then the previous ones.
<br />

<br />
Note that in this system it was actually posible to go negative in certain circumstances like looting the wrong item and it would have worked fine for flag values as well if a member lacked enough points.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Banished Soul Talc
<br />

<br />
