                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Loot Councils are hard on the people allocating loot.
<br />

<br />
As an aside, the %-based system was designed to approximate loot-council like approaches to loot distribution with as little overhead/human bias as possible.
<br />

<br />
The thing it doesn't do is see the size of the upgrade: this is left up to the player.
<br />

<br />
Anti-social players can block minor upgrades of other players by asking to loot everything as major upgrades, up to and including destroying them.  So it isn't bullet proof.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="row1" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="nav"><a href="#top" class="nav">Back to top</a></span></td>
