		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row1"><a name="100649"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Axterix EnObelix</span></span><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_offline.gif" border="0" align="absbottom" alt="Offline" title="Offline" /><div class="gensmall"><img src="images/ranks/rank_7.gif" alt="<b><center>Master</b></center>" title="<b><center>Master</b></center>" border="0" /><br /><b><center>Master</b></center></div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Joined:&nbsp;12 Aug 2003</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Total posts:&nbsp;484</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Gender:&nbsp;Unknown</div></td>
                <td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a href="viewtopic.php?p=100649#100649"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Thu Apr 07, 2005 5:11 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td align="right" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=100649"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td></tr></table></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Anti-social players can block minor upgrades of other players by asking to loot everything as major upgrades, up to and including destroying them. So it isn't bullet proof.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
We never had an issue like that.  If such a thing happens in your guild, it has issues and a few members that shouldn't be there.  Of course, we looked at the when quite a bit.  Such a player would wind up destroying some gear and getting nothing.  And there's the risk that someone on the council knows your real gear.  From experience, we often did.  Anti-social players tend not to join casual family type guilds anyway...socialness is the main perk.
<br />

<br />
If one was worried about it, one could have all members keep an update magelo/post of gear.  We had that for our guild, not for any fear of issues like this, but because it made it easier for members to hand down gear they outgrew to other guildies.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I would assume this is why you have them link what they would be upgrading? This way the Loot Council can decide where the upgrade is best used.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Be careful with that.  Best used isn't the best criteria a lot of the time.  For example, your guild would benefit the most if you made one real good tank (as long as he's the type that's always there, won't leave the guild), with a secondary backup.  However, your other tanks would not appreciate that.  Got to spread the love around.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
