                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally my guild gives 1 point for every 30 minutes during a raid, with 2 points for actually being present in zone when the raids "official" time starts. You can spend up to twice your total points, so if you had 100 points, you can bid 200. Its to allow people to get items they normally wouldnt have the points to get. All those who want the item send a tell to one of the officers who cant use it/or has it already, stating how many points they are willing to bid. We have used this system for over 4 years, and it works. While we dont have a system in place for the points to decay over time, if you dont raid and earn at least 135 points in the past 30 days, your % of how much you can bid starts dropping, so that at the end of a month of not playing, you have 1 point to bid period, instead of the thousands you might have saved up.
<br />

<br />
 While it sounds like people can collect massive amounts of points, most in guild hover around 250, with the exception of 4 or so people who are currently at 5k+ lol. But those are the ones who raid constantly, and already have everything they really want. Hm, rarely if ever have had any real troubles with it.
<br />

<br />
 And for older content where everyone simply HATES doing it, like time, we used to do a scaling point system, 1st we tried couldnt bid on anything if you joined after phase 3, that didnt really work, then they tried a 27 points for a whole clearing, that kinda worked, now GL has said if you REALLY want to do time for "easy cheap upgrades" you better show up when raid starts not when phase 3 is cleared hehe.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Vahen, Dark Elf Enchanter
<br />
E'ci Server (Arete)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
